Cell.Data: An interaction during which services are provided to the patient
An interaction between a patient and healthcare provider(s) for the purpose of providing healthcare service(s) or assessing the health status of a patient.
Identifier(s) by which this encounter is known
planned | arrived | in-progress | onleave | finished | cancelled
No clear equivalent in V2.x; active/finished could be inferred from PV1-44, PV1-45, PV2-24; inactive could be inferred from PV2-16

The current status is always found in the current version of the resource. This status history permits the encounter resource to contain the status history without the needing to read through the historical versions of the resource, or even have the server store them.
planned | arrived | in-progress | onleave | finished | cancelled
The time that the episode was in the specified status
Specific type of encounter (e.g. e-mail consultation, surgical day-care, skilled nursing, rehabilitation)
Since there are many ways to further classify encounters, this element is 0..*
The patient present at the encounter
While the encounter is always about the patient, the patient may not actually be known in all contexts of use
An episode of care that this encounter should be recorded against

Where a specific encounter should be classified as a part of a specific episode of care this field should be used. This association can facilitate grouping of related encounters together for a specific purpose, such as govt reporting, or issue tracking.
List of participants involved in the encounter
The main practitioner responsible for providing the service
Period of time during the encounter participant was present
The period of time that the specified participant was present during the encounter. These can overlap or be sub-sets of the overall encounters period
Persons involved in the encounter other than the patient
The appointment that scheduled this encounter
SCH-1-placer appointment ID / SCH-2-filler appointment ID
The start and end time of the encounter
The start and end time of the encounter
If not (yet) known, the end of the Period may be omitted
Quantity of time the encounter lasted
Quantity of time the encounter lasted. This excludes the time during leaves of absence.
May differ from the time the Encounter.period lasted because of leave of absence.
(PV1-45 less PV1-44) iff ( (PV1-44 not empty) and (PV1-45 not empty) ); units in minutes
Reason the encounter takes place, expressed as a code. For admissions, this can be used for a coded admission diagnosis.

EVN-4-event reason code / PV2-3-admit reason (note: PV2-3 is nominally constrained to inpatient admissions; V2.x makes no vocabulary suggestions for PV2-3; would not expect PV2 segment or PV2-3 to be in use in all implementations )
Reason the encounter takes place, as specified using information from another resource. For admissions, this is the admission diagnosis.
Indicates the urgency of the encounter
Details about an admission to a clinic
Details about an admission to a clinic
Tests to be done before admission
The location from which the patient came before admission
From where patient was admitted (physician referral, transfer)
Period during which the patient was admitted
Period during which the patient was admitted
May differ from start + length, since length excludes leaves of absence.
PV2-11-actual length of inpatient stay / PV1-44-admit date/time / PV1-45-discharge date/time
Where the patient stays during this encounter
The bed that is assigned to the patient
Period during which the patient was assigned the bed
Track patients reported dietary restrictions to help with catering requirements
PV1-15-ambulatory status / OBR-30-transportation mode / OBR-43-planned patient transport comment
Location to which the patient is discharged
Category or kind of location after discharge
The final diagnosis given a patient before release from the hospital after all testing, surgery, and workup are complete
Whether this hospitalization is a readmission
Need a harmonization proposal for this
List of locations the patient has been at
List of locations at which the patient has been
The location where the encounter takes place
PV1-3-assigned patient location / PV1-6-prior patient location / PV1-11-temporary location / PV1-42-pending location / PV1-43-prior temporary location
The status of the participants presence at the specified location during the period specified. If the participant is is no longer at the location, then the period will have an end date/time
Time period during which the patient was present at the location

PV1-10-hospital service / PL.6 Person Location Type & PL.1 Point of Care (note: V2.x definition is "the treatment or type of surgery that the patient is scheduled to receive"; seems slightly out of alignment with the concept name 'hospital service'. Would not trust that implementations apply this semantic by default)
Another Encounter this encounter is part of
Another Encounter of which this encounter is a part of (administratively or in time).
